1
00:00:06,874 --> 00:00:09,777
⟨Spending days filled with love with 50 people who love me→

2
00:00:09,844 --> 00:00:11,779
Detective Manami Tanizaki⟩

3
00:00:11,846 --> 00:00:16,784
⟨While being toyed with by Kamiki, who claims to be the mastermind behind the My Love serial murders →

4
00:00:16,851 --> 00:00:20,788
Manami's ex-husband Kiryu emerges as a suspect⟩

5
00:00:20,855 --> 00:00:25,793
⟨And Manami seems to be disturbed by the sacred tree...⟩

6
00:00:25,860 --> 00:00:31,298
⟨Manami, let's just stop saying bad things⟩

7
00:00:31,365 --> 00:00:33,300
(Kiyosumi) Come on, do it quickly. >> \Yes/

8
00:00:33,367 --> 00:00:35,803
(Kiyosumi) You can just put it all in now.

9
00:00:35,870 --> 00:00:37,304
\yes/

10
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:41,308
Kuroiwa: Move your hands. (Kuroiwa) I'm sorry.

11
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:43,811
(Takamine's voice) As a suspect in a serial murder→

12
00:00:43,878 --> 00:00:47,815
Former First Investigation Division detective Toru Kiryu has surfaced.

13
00:00:47,882 --> 00:00:52,319
Location unknown. Tracking teams are already on the move.

14
00:00:52,386 --> 00:00:55,322
(Manami) Leaving fingerprints...

15
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:58,325
I wonder if Kiryu would make a mistake like that.

16
00:00:58,392 --> 00:01:03,264
(Takamine) Maybe they just didn't have enough time to destroy the evidence.

17
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:06,834
(Manami) Kiryu has no motive.

18
00:01:10,337 --> 00:01:12,773
>> Unskilled →

19
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:15,776
Possessive desire.

20
00:01:15,843 --> 00:01:18,279
(Manami) No, no…｡

21
00:01:18,345 --> 00:01:23,284
You don't love me enough to do that.

22
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:27,855
>> I was talking about Manami-san as an "important person."

23
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:36,297
(Yuriko) Sorry Kiryu-kun's computer password →

24
00:01:36,363 --> 00:01:38,799
I don't quite understand it.

25
00:01:38,866 --> 00:01:41,302
Do you understand?

26
00:01:41,368 --> 00:01:43,304
(Manami) I'll try it once.

27
00:01:43,370 --> 00:01:45,806
Well…｡

28
00:01:45,873 --> 00:02:00,321
♪～

29
00:02:00,387 --> 00:02:03,757
>> What number?

30
00:02:03,824 --> 00:02:07,261
(Manami) Wedding anniversary.

31
00:02:07,328 --> 00:02:11,265
Haven't you changed since you were married?

32
00:02:11,332 --> 00:02:13,767
>> I've been thinking about it for a long time.

33
00:02:13,834 --> 00:02:16,270
Origin of the name Ai-chan.

34
00:02:16,337 --> 00:02:21,275
This name doesn't seem to be common even in the detective industry.

35
00:02:21,342 --> 00:02:24,778
There are very few places where this is clearly defined.

36
00:02:24,845 --> 00:02:28,782
(Manami) Huh? Something like “catch me”?

37
00:02:28,849 --> 00:02:32,786
He wasn't that lame though.

38
00:02:32,853 --> 00:02:37,358
>>Actually, I want it to stop...

39
00:02:40,361 --> 00:02:43,864
(Manami) Have you ever met Toru Kiryu?

40
00:02:47,368 --> 00:02:52,373
(Kamiki) There is now a possibility that Kiryu is a suspect.

41
00:02:54,375 --> 00:02:58,812
The investigation is moving in the wrong direction.

42
00:02:58,879 --> 00:03:04,251
And for those who are having a hard time.

43
00:03:04,318 --> 00:03:10,324
If this continues, you will be released.

44
00:03:12,326 --> 00:03:15,763
Please find it.

45
00:03:15,829 --> 00:03:19,333
Proof that I'm Ai-chan.

46
00:03:20,834 --> 00:03:23,270
(Manami) I'll find it.

47
00:03:23,337 --> 00:03:26,273
Even if you don't say it.

48
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:29,276
absolute.

49
00:03:29,343 --> 00:03:33,280
(Kuroiwa) Everyone is looking for evidence that Mr. Kiryu did this.

50
00:03:33,347 --> 00:03:36,784
(Manami) Well, I guess it will happen.

51
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:39,286
(Kuroiwa) Would you like to wash it again?

52
00:03:39,353 --> 00:03:41,789
Proof that Kamiki did it.

53
00:03:41,855 --> 00:03:43,357
(Manami) Yes.

54
00:03:44,858 --> 00:03:46,293
(Kuroiwa) Yes...

55
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,795
(Manami) Huh?

56
00:03:47,861 --> 00:03:49,363
(Kuroiwa) Thank you.

57
00:03:50,864 --> 00:03:54,802
(Manami) Did you see any strange cars or suspicious people?

58
00:03:54,868 --> 00:04:03,744
♪～

59
00:04:03,811 --> 00:04:06,313
(Manami) Huh...｡

60
00:04:10,818 --> 00:04:13,254
(Manami) What? Released!?

61
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:16,257
>> Emails sent instructions to previous perpetrators.

62
00:04:16,323 --> 00:04:19,760
Murder weapon purchase history.

63
00:04:19,827 --> 00:04:23,764
How to judge Kiryu-san as Ai-chan instead of Kamiki→

64
00:04:23,831 --> 00:04:26,767
There is more than enough evidence.

65
00:04:26,834 --> 00:04:29,770
(Kuroiwa) But there's still a possibility that Kamiki is an accomplice...

66
00:04:29,837 --> 00:04:32,773
>> Evidence supporting the contact between Kamiki and Kiryu is →

67
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:35,776
Nothing is mentioned.

68
00:04:35,843 --> 00:04:41,348
It is highly likely that Kamiki has nothing to do with this incident.

69
00:04:48,856 --> 00:04:53,360
Too bad I didn't make it in time.

70
00:04:54,862 --> 00:04:57,297
(Manami) Yes.

71
00:04:57,364 --> 00:05:02,870
>> It was just a little bit more, though.

72
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:14,748
In a little while →

73
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:18,252
I felt like my hatred was about to turn over.

74
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:20,821
(sound of standing up)

75
00:05:25,826 --> 00:05:27,761
(Kuroiwa) Don't get carried away. >> Hahaha...｡

76
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:30,264
Did you get angry?

77
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:32,266
(Kuroiwa) You did it, right?

78
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,768
Say "I did it"! >> I keep saying that!

79
00:05:34,835 --> 00:05:38,272
What I couldn't prove was →

80
00:05:38,338 --> 00:05:40,841
It’s you guys!

81
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:46,280
(Kuroiwa) What is it?

82
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:51,785
That's no good, unless you're the culprit.

83
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:56,290
>>It's really important.

84
00:05:56,356 --> 00:05:58,792
Manami-san.

85
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:00,861
(The sound of running footsteps)

86
00:06:12,306 --> 00:06:15,743
(Iori) I'm very sorry.

87
00:06:15,809 --> 00:06:17,811
home….

88
00:06:31,992 --> 00:06:33,861
(Kuroiwa) I'm sorry.

89
00:06:33,927 --> 00:06:36,363
>>I'm a police officer at heart→

90
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:39,366
I can't ignore the fact that the public order is being disrupted.

91
00:06:39,433 --> 00:06:42,369
(Kuroiwa) Um, what an apology…｡ (Sound of placing)

92
00:06:42,436 --> 00:06:48,375
I'll be sure to impose a punishment after that...

93
00:06:48,442 --> 00:06:50,444
(Kuroiwa) Kejime?

94
00:06:54,948 --> 00:06:59,953
>> Does it really matter if Kamiki isn't the culprit?

95
00:07:01,955 --> 00:07:05,893
(Kuroiwa) I don't want to think it's Kiryu-san.

96
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:09,897
>> Hmph... Well, to be honest, me too →

97
00:07:09,963 --> 00:07:13,400
I wish Kamiki was the culprit.

98
00:07:13,467 --> 00:07:16,403
(Kuroiwa) Huh? >> As expected from Manami →

99
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:19,907
I feel like if Kiryu were the culprit, it would be broken.

100
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:22,476
I think it's quite dangerous.

101
00:07:24,978 --> 00:07:27,414
Well, for me →

102
00:07:27,481 --> 00:07:29,917
The person who gets in the way of Manami's life is →

103
00:07:29,983 --> 00:07:33,420
I think everyone should just disappear.

104
00:07:33,487 --> 00:07:37,991
Whether it's Kamiki or Kiryu.

105
00:07:41,495 --> 00:07:43,430
That's why→

106
00:07:43,497 --> 00:07:46,433
Trying to make Kamiki the culprit is out of the question.

107
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:48,936
It's straight up a false accusation.

108
00:07:49,002 --> 00:07:51,939
(Kuroiwa) Yes, sorry.

109
00:07:52,005 --> 00:07:54,942
>> Don't go crazy with jealousy.

110
00:07:55,008 --> 00:07:58,011
Because I'm not in Manami's eyes.

111
00:08:02,516 --> 00:08:07,020
Huh, that's all.

112
00:08:11,024 --> 00:08:14,962
Do you want to eat hot pot?

113
00:08:15,028 --> 00:08:16,964
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

114
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:20,467
(Monitor) (Counselor) I think it would be better for that person to stop.

115
00:08:20,534 --> 00:08:23,971
(Manami) Ah... that's right.

116
00:08:24,037 --> 00:08:29,476
I know, but what should I do...

117
00:08:29,543 --> 00:08:33,914
(Monitor) Manami-san, are you hitting the key points on your brain?

118
00:08:33,981 --> 00:08:36,416
(Manami) Yes, yes! It's already hard.

119
00:08:36,483 --> 00:08:38,418
I'm holding it down hard.

120
00:08:38,485 --> 00:08:40,921
But is this effective?

121
00:08:40,988 --> 00:08:43,924
(Monitor) Gangan Gangan If it doesn't work, use two.

122
00:08:43,991 --> 00:08:47,928
(Monitor) If that doesn't work, then 3... (Manami) If 2 doesn't work, then 3 Gan Gan...

123
00:08:47,995 --> 00:08:49,930
>> What are you doing? (Manami) Wow~ I was surprised!

124
00:08:49,997 --> 00:08:52,432
Trespassing! >> No, the door was unlocked.

125
00:08:52,499 --> 00:08:56,937
(Manami) Just knock a little. >> No, it's puberty!

126
00:08:57,004 --> 00:09:00,941
(Manami) Hey, Kuroiwa-kun, what's wrong?

127
00:09:01,008 --> 00:09:03,944
(Kuroiwa) What were you doing? now.

128
00:09:04,011 --> 00:09:06,947
(Manami) Huh? no….

129
00:09:07,014 --> 00:09:10,450
I haven't done anything in particular.

130
00:09:10,517 --> 00:09:13,020
a! Let's make a pot. >> Ah, let's do that.

131
00:09:14,521 --> 00:09:16,957
(Manami) It's delicious! (Yuriko) Eat it, eat it!

132
00:09:17,024 --> 00:09:19,459
(Kuroiwa) What exactly is this pot?

133
00:09:19,526 --> 00:09:21,461
Are hot pot and fried chicken okay?

134
00:09:21,528 --> 00:09:23,964
(Manami) It takes a lot of time because it's fried and then boiled.

135
00:09:24,031 --> 00:09:25,966
>> It's a good thing you took the extra effort to kill him.

136
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,468
(Manami) Thank you! >>I might surprisingly like it.

137
00:09:28,535 --> 00:09:30,470
It feels like everything is impermanent.

138
00:09:30,537 --> 00:09:32,472
(Kuroiwa) What do you think of the taste? That's it. >> Huh?

139
00:09:32,539 --> 00:09:34,408
(Manami) Well, what about you, Kuroiwa-kun?

140
00:09:34,474 --> 00:09:37,911
>> Eat, eat...｡ (Manami) Eat! Eat! Eat!

141
00:09:37,978 --> 00:09:40,414
(Kuroiwa) You're doing well.

142
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,916
(Manami) Huh? It won't be the same as usual.

143
00:09:42,983 --> 00:09:45,485
(Kuroiwa) Isn't it strange that things are the same as usual?

144
00:09:47,988 --> 00:09:49,923
(Manami) I guess so...｡

145
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:52,426
(Kuroiwa) Mr. Kiryu became a suspect and suspected Kamiki →

146
00:09:52,492 --> 00:09:54,995
He was released.

147
00:09:57,998 --> 00:10:00,434
>> Ah~ Shall we eat some fried chicken?

148
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,437
(Kuroiwa) What do you think about Kamiki?

149
00:10:03,503 --> 00:10:06,506
>> I went crazy with jealousy again.

150
00:10:08,508 --> 00:10:12,446
(Manami) What are you talking about? You have a surprisingly romantic brain.

151
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,915
Let's get the mayonnaise...

152
00:10:14,982 --> 00:10:17,417
(Kuroiwa) Manami-san should have her favorite hairstyle →

153
00:10:17,484 --> 00:10:19,987
Desperately press the pressure point that suppresses your sexual desire.

154
00:10:21,488 --> 00:10:25,926
We were talking about Kamiki earlier, I think.

155
00:10:25,993 --> 00:10:28,929
(Manami) No, no, no.

156
00:10:28,996 --> 00:10:33,500
Are you a suspect? (Kuroiwa) I'm not even a suspect, but right now.

157
00:10:36,436 --> 00:10:38,372
I'm sorry.

158
00:10:38,438 --> 00:10:40,374
(Yuriko) It's okay, it's okay.

159
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:43,377
It was something new and interesting haha.

160
00:10:43,443 --> 00:10:47,881
But it all backfired.

161
00:10:47,948 --> 00:10:50,884
It was like me when I talked to my daughter.

162
00:10:50,951 --> 00:10:53,387
(Kuroiwa) Daughter? >> Hehehe…｡

163
00:10:53,453 --> 00:10:56,890
If I told you to go to bed early, you would force yourself to stay up all night →

164
00:10:56,957 --> 00:10:59,893
I never wore clothes that I said looked good on me again.

165
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,895
(Kuroiwa) Haha…｡

166
00:11:01,962 --> 00:11:06,400
Are you in a rebellious period, Manami-san? >> Hmm...

167
00:11:06,466 --> 00:11:09,403
As for how to make it complicated, it might be more than that.

168
00:11:09,469 --> 00:11:11,405
(Kuroiwa) Haha.

169
00:11:11,471 --> 00:11:14,908
No...but there's nothing I can do about it.

170
00:11:14,975 --> 00:11:17,477
I like things like that too.

171
00:11:20,981 --> 00:11:24,418
>> It's me, Kuroiwa-kun and Manami-chan →

172
00:11:24,484 --> 00:11:27,921
I'm thinking that it's going to go well.

173
00:11:27,988 --> 00:11:30,424
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

174
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:32,926
Ah, no... it's not there.

175
00:11:32,993 --> 00:11:36,363
The other day, I got dumped before I could even confess my feelings.

176
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:40,934
There's nothing like that, regardless of the police or anything.

177
00:11:42,436 --> 00:11:45,872
>> I'm sure Manami-chan will change too.

178
00:11:45,939 --> 00:11:49,876
Maybe things are starting to change now.

179
00:11:49,943 --> 00:11:53,380
(Kuroiwa) Thanks to Kamiki...?

180
00:11:53,447 --> 00:11:56,383
>> But than Kamiki→

181
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:58,885
Kuroiwa-kun is good.

182
00:11:58,952 --> 00:12:01,888
(Kuroiwa) Are you being praised? that.

183
00:12:01,955 --> 00:12:05,892
>> Only people who can prioritize Manami-chan above all else →

184
00:12:05,959 --> 00:12:08,395
If I could love Manami →

185
00:12:08,462 --> 00:12:10,964
I'm sure this won't happen.

186
00:12:12,966 --> 00:12:15,902
Good luck hehehe...

187
00:12:15,969 --> 00:12:17,971
(Kuroiwa) Usu.

188
00:12:19,973 --> 00:12:23,977
>> Is this the end?

189
00:12:25,479 --> 00:12:28,415
(Kuroiwa) That's true.

190
00:12:28,482 --> 00:12:31,485
>>I wanted to talk more.

191
00:12:34,421 --> 00:12:36,923
(Manami) Me too.

192
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:41,928
>> That makes me happy.

193
00:12:47,934 --> 00:12:50,437
this….

194
00:12:54,441 --> 00:12:56,943
I'll forget about it.

195
00:13:04,451 --> 00:13:08,955
(Kuroiwa) If we can get testimony, I think we should meet.

196
00:13:10,957 --> 00:13:14,461
(Manami) I guess you weren't the kind of person who cared about ethics.

197
00:13:19,466 --> 00:13:24,971
(Kuroiwa) It's the police's job to deliver lost items.

198
00:13:30,477 --> 00:13:32,479
(Manami) I understand.

199
00:13:37,651 --> 00:13:41,154
(Manami) Huh…｡

200
00:13:42,355 --> 00:13:46,293
>> Sorry to have kept you waiting! (Manami) Ah... hello.

201
00:13:46,359 --> 00:13:48,862
>> Let's go. (Manami) Yes.

202
00:13:52,866 --> 00:13:56,303
(Manami) 《Never be shaken》

203
00:14:01,308 --> 00:14:04,744
>> It's been a long time since I wanted to breathe outside air.

204
00:14:04,811 --> 00:14:07,747
Hey, do you mean the air of Shaba?

205
00:14:07,814 --> 00:14:10,250
(Manami) No, you came in by yourself.

206
00:14:10,317 --> 00:14:12,319
>> Hehe... Indeed.

207
00:14:15,822 --> 00:14:19,826
(Manami) Please tell me your motive for turning yourself in.

208
00:14:21,828 --> 00:14:25,265
>> Ah! Soft cream.

209
00:14:25,332 --> 00:14:27,834
do you like it? I'll buy it.

210
00:14:31,838 --> 00:14:37,277
(Manami) 《Even if I see a smile that looks different from the one in the interrogation room...》

211
00:14:37,344 --> 00:14:39,279
>> Hahaha…｡ (Manami) Thank you.

212
00:14:39,346 --> 00:14:41,281
>> Ah! (Manami) Ah! Ha…｡

213
00:14:41,348 --> 00:14:43,283
>> Sorry. (Manami) Oh no...｡

214
00:14:43,350 --> 00:14:48,288
>> Ah, but it's safe here... haha.

215
00:14:48,355 --> 00:14:50,790
There was something to wipe...

216
00:14:50,857 --> 00:14:55,795
(Manami) 《Calculate everything... Don't believe it》

217
00:14:55,862 --> 00:14:57,297
>> Ha!

218
00:14:57,364 --> 00:14:59,799
(Manami) 《This is part of the investigation》

219
00:14:59,866 --> 00:15:02,302
《To extract information》

220
00:15:02,369 --> 00:15:04,371
that! >> Yes!

221
00:15:07,874 --> 00:15:12,312
(Manami) 《It's over! What do you do all day? I"

222
00:15:12,379 --> 00:15:17,317
>> Well, it was fun...

223
00:15:17,384 --> 00:15:22,822
(Manami) 《Recently, I have been shaken by this man.》

224
00:15:22,889 --> 00:15:26,826
《Sometimes I say I don't like it, sometimes I say I like it.''

225
00:15:26,893 --> 00:15:30,330
I thought he was the man who killed the people he cared about →

226
00:15:30,397 --> 00:15:33,333
Do something to help the people you care about.

227
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:37,337
>> [I feel like I could do anything for that person]

228
00:15:37,404 --> 00:15:40,340
(Manami) 《My heart is busy and shaking→

229
00:15:40,407 --> 00:15:42,842
If you touch me carelessly to restrain me...》

230
00:15:42,909 --> 00:15:46,346
>> [I... will not leave you]

231
00:15:46,413 --> 00:15:48,415
(Manami) 《More shaking》

232
00:15:51,418 --> 00:15:53,787
(Manami) 《I noticed》

233
00:15:53,853 --> 00:15:59,292
《I feel comfortable》

234
00:15:59,359 --> 00:16:03,797
《Like a baby seeking its cradle→

235
00:16:03,863 --> 00:16:06,366
This man...》

236
00:16:09,369 --> 00:16:11,371
(Manami) Ha…｡

237
00:16:12,872 --> 00:16:16,309
Can we get to the point?

238
00:16:16,376 --> 00:16:21,381
>> Yes, sorry to have kept you waiting, please ask me anything.

239
00:16:23,383 --> 00:16:27,887
(Manami) You're not Ai-chan, right?

240
00:16:29,389 --> 00:16:31,391
>> Why?

241
00:16:32,892 --> 00:16:37,397
(Manami) I'm not interested in people enough to kill them.

242
00:16:39,899 --> 00:16:43,336
I don't love you enough to do this.

243
00:16:43,403 --> 00:16:45,405
About me.

244
00:16:49,409 --> 00:16:51,911
>>I'm half right.

245
00:16:54,848 --> 00:16:57,784
(Manami) Why did you turn yourself in?

246
00:16:57,851 --> 00:16:59,853
>> Because I want to help.

247
00:17:01,855 --> 00:17:05,358
(Manami) What kind of person is Kamiki-san?

248
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:11,364
>> That's... a rather difficult question.

249
00:17:13,366 --> 00:17:16,302
That's right...

250
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:20,306
Maybe he's like a straw man.

251
00:17:20,373 --> 00:17:22,308
(Manami) Huh?

252
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:25,311
>> If this is a standalone →

253
00:17:25,378 --> 00:17:28,314
Isn't it just a hollow?

254
00:17:28,381 --> 00:17:31,818
(Manami) I need something to drink.

255
00:17:31,885 --> 00:17:35,822
>> I can't find a drink to drink →

256
00:17:35,889 --> 00:17:38,324
It is in the middle of the day.

257
00:17:38,391 --> 00:17:40,827
I thought you were the same.

258
00:17:40,894 --> 00:17:43,329
(Manami) Huh?

259
00:17:43,396 --> 00:17:46,332
>>But it was different.

260
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:51,337
It changes color when mixed with various drinks →

261
00:17:51,404 --> 00:17:54,774
Bitten and hurt→

262
00:17:54,841 --> 00:17:58,278
It became limp...

263
00:17:58,344 --> 00:18:02,282
(Manami) Isn't that already trash?

264
00:18:02,348 --> 00:18:06,286
>> But it's nowhere.

265
00:18:06,352 --> 00:18:11,791
It has become a straw that can be seen on its own.

266
00:18:11,858 --> 00:18:16,296
(Manami) Is that a compliment? >> I'm praising you.

267
00:18:16,362 --> 00:18:19,299
From a pure straw →

268
00:18:19,365 --> 00:18:22,302
It has great taste.

269
00:18:22,368 --> 00:18:25,305
(Manami) I'm not really happy.

270
00:18:25,371 --> 00:18:27,874
For example, haven't you failed?

271
00:18:31,878 --> 00:18:33,880
(Manami) Hey...

272
00:18:35,882 --> 00:18:39,319
>> Isn't that enough?

273
00:18:39,385 --> 00:18:41,888
Don't look for a drink.

274
00:18:45,391 --> 00:18:48,328
This is this →

275
00:18:48,394 --> 00:18:52,332
I feel like it has taste.

276
00:18:52,398 --> 00:18:54,834
It's uneven.

277
00:18:56,336 --> 00:18:58,771
(Manami) This also looks like garbage...

278
00:18:58,838 --> 00:19:02,842
>> Good! If it's trash, it's trash.

279
00:19:06,846 --> 00:19:10,283
If I were with you →

280
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:13,353
I think it's clear.

281
00:19:16,356 --> 00:19:18,858
My shape.

282
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:25,865
What am I here for?

283
00:19:30,370 --> 00:19:34,807
Won't you fall in love with me...

284
00:19:34,874 --> 00:19:37,810
Only about me.

285
00:19:37,877 --> 00:19:49,889
♪～

286
00:19:51,391 --> 00:19:55,328
(Manami) I like it so much that I started nuzzling it right away.

287
00:19:57,330 --> 00:20:01,768
I decide my shape.

288
00:20:01,834 --> 00:20:10,276
♪～

289
00:20:10,343 --> 00:20:14,847
>> I see... That's unfortunate.

290
00:20:20,353 --> 00:20:22,288
(Manami) The person who turned himself in was →

291
00:20:22,355 --> 00:20:26,292
Is it to stop Ai-chan?

292
00:20:26,359 --> 00:20:30,296
>> That's right... That was the question.

293
00:20:30,363 --> 00:20:33,800
(Manami) I've always wondered about this.

294
00:20:33,866 --> 00:20:36,803
If you are not Ai-chan→

295
00:20:36,869 --> 00:20:40,807
Why was he able to talk about his crimes in detail?

296
00:20:40,873 --> 00:20:43,309
Why as soon as you turned yourself in →

297
00:20:43,376 --> 00:20:46,379
Has the serial killing stopped?

298
00:20:48,381 --> 00:20:50,817
I’m in touch with Ai-chan →

299
00:20:50,883 --> 00:20:54,253
You who knew about the crime plan→

300
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:58,257
He turned himself in, blaming Ai-chan for the crime.

301
00:20:58,324 --> 00:21:00,760
>>What do you think?

302
00:21:00,827 --> 00:21:04,263
(Manami) What you really want to help is →

303
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:07,834
It's not me, it's Ai-chan.

304
00:21:11,337 --> 00:21:15,341
(Manami) Who are you? It's Ai-chan.

305
00:21:18,845 --> 00:21:23,282
>> If I could give you just one hint →

306
00:21:23,349 --> 00:21:26,285
Ai-chan →

307
00:21:26,352 --> 00:21:29,355
A person who cares about you.

308
00:21:32,358 --> 00:21:35,795
(Manami) I'm sorry.

309
00:21:35,862 --> 00:21:40,366
I might not have time for quizzes anymore.

310
00:21:41,868 --> 00:21:46,305
>> Can I have your handkerchief back?

311
00:21:46,372 --> 00:21:47,874
(Manami) Huh?

312
00:21:49,375 --> 00:21:52,311
>> The correct answer is →

313
00:21:52,378 --> 00:21:54,814
After using the restroom.

314
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:04,824
(Manami) Please don't run away.

315
00:22:12,332 --> 00:22:16,269
(footsteps)

316
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:19,272
(Kuroiwa) Huh? What happened?

317
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:21,274
>> You know...

318
00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:23,276
(Kuroiwa) Yes.

319
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:25,278
>> From the suspect in this case →

320
00:22:25,344 --> 00:22:29,282
Is it okay to remove Manami?

321
00:22:29,348 --> 00:22:31,284
(Kuroiwa) Eh...

322
00:22:31,351 --> 00:22:41,294
♪～

323
00:22:41,361 --> 00:22:43,362
>> Kuh…｡

324
00:22:47,366 --> 00:22:51,304
Ugh...ha...｡

325
00:22:51,371 --> 00:22:54,240
Hmm…｡

326
00:22:54,307 --> 00:23:07,320
♪～
